OL,5,CIII
OL,7,FIt went on to say: "I will not alter
OL,8,Fmy physicality to explore it. I will
OL,9,Fnot be playing Richard with a visible
OL,10,For physical impairment, and we will
OL,11,Fframe this production in such a way as
OL,12,Fto make it very clear the lens through
OL,13,Fwhich this interpretation is being
OL,14,Fexplored.
OL,16,F"This production does not equal a
OL,17,Fpermanent revision of the play or the
OL,18,Feternal erasure of the character's
OL,19,Fimpairment, or a rewriting of a
OL,20,Fhistorical figure.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G3/9
