OL,3,CShakespeare's Globe theatre defends
OL,4,Ccasting non-disabled actor as Richard
OL,5,CIII
OL,7,F"I acknowledge that for many, Richard
OL,8,FIII is an iconic disabled figure. I
OL,9,Funderstand that this feels like a
OL,10,Fmissed opportunity for a disabled
OL,11,Fartist to play a disabled character on
OL,12,Fa major UK stage, but it will come
OL,13,Faround again."
OL,15,FThe Globe's statement follows backlash
OL,16,Ffrom actors with disabilities who
OL,17,Fdisagreed with Terry's casting.
OL,19,FIn the play, Richard III describes
OL,20,Fhimself as "deformed, unfinish'd".
