OL,5,CIII
OL,7,F"There's been incredible progress made
OL,8,Facross all facets and routes of the
OL,9,Findustry regarding disabled inclusion,
OL,10,Fincluding the casting of disabled
OL,11,Factors across disabled and
OL,12,Ftraditionally non-disabled roles. But
OL,13,Fthis role belongs to us. It is
OL,14,Foffensive and distasteful for Richard
OL,15,Fto be portrayed by someone outside the
OL,16,Fcommunity."
